&lt;p&gt;
	We have engaged a Local Food Safety Consultant to oversee the Food Safety Management System and to carry out additional food hygiene training for staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
	There was some confusion between staff regarding the Use By/Best Before dates on food items. All kitchen staff are now aware of the need for communication during changeover of staff. With this in mind, we have implemented a new day-dot stock control system. All in-house prepared foods will be allocated a maximum shelf life of 3 days, to include the day of production or from opening, unless the manufacturers` instructions state otherwise. We will carry out stock checks daily and any foods that will exceed their Use By dates will be discarded before midnight to ensure that foods are not offered for sale the following morning with expired shelf life. A new shelf life notice is displayed in the kitchen with the relevant instructions clearly shown.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;
		There was some confusion regarding the food surface disinfectants. We now use ready made disinfectants with clear instructions for use on the bottles. The importance of the contact time has been clearly explained to staff. This product complies with BS EN 13697 requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;
		Staff have received clear instructions that any ambient foods are stored at the correct temperatures after opening as they may become high-risk foods requiring strict temperature control.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;
		A more robust system of checking damaged/worn equipment is now in place to ensure all equipment is in good condition so as no to contaminate food.&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;div&gt;
		A new Documented Food Safety Management System has been put in place and is checked by management to ensure staff are following the company&amp;#39;s policies at all times. There are clear, written instructions for safe shelf life of foods. We will only use chemicals that are ready to use from the manufacturer and the written instructions will be applied at all times.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
